<subSubSection lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,405,2015]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1953,1979]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
Despite a relatively large amount of variation in the structures of the male genitalia, the color pattern and external morphology are remarkably similar among species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,151,213]" box="[199,1437,151,177]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">The four species included in the phylogenetic analysis here were strongly supported as a monophyletic group.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1437,151,213]" box="[151,1075,187,213]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
The relationship of the genus to other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zahniser" authorityYear="2021" box="[578,660,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Faltala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[578,660,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Faltala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group genera was not well-resolved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,356,258,285]" box="[151,356,258,285]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,356,258,285]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Included species:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,595,331,501]" box="[151,570,331,358]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
